The issue seems to be with the syntax of the formulas, specifically with referencing the 'Data' sheet. The test formula `='Data'!A1` worked, but the others did not.

To fix this, I will update the formulas to use the correct syntax. I will use the `='Data'!` syntax to reference the 'Data' sheet.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The issue is with the syntax of the formulas. The correct syntax is `='Data'!`. I will update the formulas to use this syntax.",
  "plan": "Update the formulas to use the correct syntax.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 << 'EOF'\nfrom openpyxl import load_workbook\n\nwb = load_workbook('protein_expression.xlsx')\nws_task = wb['Task']\n\nfor row in range(11, 21):\n    for col in range(3, 13):\n        formula = f\"=IFERROR(INDEX('Data'!$D$2:$AZ$201,MATCH($A{row},'Data'!$A$2:$A$201,0),MATCH(${{col}}$10,'Data'!$D$1:$AZ$1,0)),\"\")\"\n        ws_task.cell(row, col).value = formula\n\nwb.save('protein_expression.xlsx')\nprint(\"File saved.\")\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
```
